Fourteen persons at station community, near Idon town in Kajuru Local Government Area of Kaduna State have been kidnapped by bandits in the early hours on Saturday. A source in Kajuru Local Government Council gave the names of the victims as Abdullahi, Yakubu Isah, Samson Julius, Angelina Julius, Pasema Daniel and Junior. He added that others are Bobo Julius, Saratu Mohammed, Asenath Sunday, Confidence Jerry, Barnaki Sunday, Moses Kenneth, Danladi Goma and Ummi Jibrin. According to him, “These are the names of abducted persons in Iri Station which we have discovered for now. The sad event happened in the early hours of today, June 4, 2022.” He told DAILY POST that some of the earlier kidnapped victims are still with the bandits, saying that their loved ones and the communities have not been able to raise the ransom.